LKCompiler Compiler (The code is still being refined)
=========================================================================================================================================================================================================================================

    This is the LKCompiler,Head-to-head love based on cbc programming language compiler.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Requirements

    To compile cbc itself:

        * JDK 1.5 or later
        * JavaCC 4.0 or later
        * ant
        * make

    To run lkc and compiled program:

        * Linux 2.4 or later
        * util-linux (ld-linux.so.2)
        * GNU libc 2.3 or later
        * GNU binutils (as, ld)


Installation


    To install all files under /usr/local/lkc:

        # sudo ./install.sh
        # sudo ln -s ../lkc/bin/lkc /usr/local/bin/lkc

    To install all files under $HOME/lkc:

        $ ./install.sh $HOME/lkc
        $ ln -s ../lkc/bin/lkc $HOME/bin/lkc


Build


    Edit build.properties for your environment and invoke make:

        $ vi build.properties
        $ make


Test

    Invoke "make test":

        $ make test

    Note that you need bash (not bourne sh) to run test scripts.
    ksh or zsh may work.


Usage


    $ lkc --help


